parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS sensor can cause the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) to malfunction, leading to loss of braking power, increased stopping distance, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The ABS warning light comes on
the brakes fail to engage or engage partially
the vehicle surges forward when braking
the brake pedal goes to the floor
excessive vibration when applying brakes
grinding noise when applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power brake booster can cause the brake pedal to become hard to press, leading to increased stopping distance and potential accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal is hard to press
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle fails to stop or stops slowly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Check Valve Failure in ABS System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the check valve in the ABS system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to loss of braking power and potential accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle fails to stop or stops slowly
the ABS warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to loss of braking power and potential accidents.
symptoms: The ABS warning light comes on
the brakes fail to engage or engage partially.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rack and Pinion Steering System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rack and pinion steering system can cause the vehicle to lose power steering, making it difficult or impossible to turn, especially to the left, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly loses power steering while making a left turn
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle's steering radius becomes too large
the steering sense is sluggish
the power steering assist is inadequate
the vehicle's steering system fails to turn left
the wheel turns 360 degrees to the left but does not move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and potentially lead to accidents, especially when it occurs without warning while driving in traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls intermittently without warning
the vehicle stalls when not warmed up
the vehicle stalls after proceeding from a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oxygen sensor can cause the check engine light to illuminate, leading to decreased fuel efficiency and potentially causing damage to the engine.
symptoms: The SES light illuminates
the oxygen sensor fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause fluid leaks, leading to engine damage and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Fluid leaks from the engine
head gaskets are leaking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unusual engine noise can be a sign of a more serious underlying issue, potentially leading to engine failure or damage.
symptoms: Noise comes from the engine while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the engine to stall or fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Gas spills onto the hot motor block
forming a puddle and vaporizing
thus forming an explosive mixture.
